# Long-chain bead polymer melt with rigid bonds constrained by fix ilves.
#
# A few (5) very long linear chains (~10000 beads each, ~50000 beads total) form
# a dense LJ melt; every backbone bond is held rigid by fix ilves.  Because the
# chains are so long, each is a single large connected constraint cluster -- the
# regime where a sparse coupled solver (ILVES) is needed and fix shake degrades.
# Companion data file: data.polymelt.

units           lj
atom_style      bond
boundary        p p p

read_data       data.polymelt
